title.en: piv: An ontology draft for describing particle image velocimetry data.

abstract.value: PIVMeta is an ontology that has been developed for the purpose of describing Particle Image Velocimetry (PIV) data. At present, its functionality is limited to planar PIV (2D2C and 2D3C) setups.

title.value: piv: An ontology draft for describing particle image velocimetry data.

definition.value: Individual processing step of a PIV measurement. The concrete subclasses should be used to clearly define the individual steps in their order to enable traceability of a PIV measurement.
Unit of measure

example.value: Typically used to describe the particle image density in a PIV image, also known as ppp (particle per pixel).

description.en: Millimeters per pixel, representing the optical magnification where the length in millimeters corresponds to the number of pixels in the image.

definition.value: A Digital Camera captures photographs or videos in a digital format.
Each flag value represents a mutually exclusive state; combinations are not used.

Background subtraction method which takes the minimum intensity at all pixels over a defined number of images from the experiment (with tracer particles) and subtracts it from each image which is taken for the PIV analysis..
A simulation that relies on physics based models, according to the Review of Materials Modelling and CWA 17284:2018.

Variable, i.e., a conventional that is employed for something to which values can be assigned (this may include different notations for the same variable including, e.g., computational representations); this is to be understood very generally, e.g., a variable may be an array or set of elements or have another kind of internal structure

A scheme defining the set of valid flag atoms and the interpretation rules for flag
values in a dataset. A scheme declares whether values are mutually exclusive

Mask data to mask out areas that should not be evaluated
An image showing Particles illuminated by a laser from a Particle Image or Tracking Velocimetry measurement.
Image Velocimetry result data, e.g. data resulting from PIV, PTV or other specialized methods. Contains at least displacement and coordinate data
A PIV or PTV image, which has been manipulated by filtering or other operations on its pixel values.
High-level PIV Analysis processing step. All other PIV Processing steps like recording, pre processing, evaluation and post processing should be references using m4i:startsWith and m4i:endsWith

Abstract description of a method for analysis, generation and transformation of data and material objects like, e.g., 'Fourier Transform Infrared Spectroscopy' or 'Molecular Dynamics Simulation'. Note that while values for relevant parameters should be provided, m4i:Method does not refer to the actual execution of the process that is described (use m4i:ProcessingStep for that), but rather a description of the underlying principle.
Processing step of measuring or calculating the background image or images.
Computer programming source code. Example: Full (compile ready) solutions, code snippet samples, scripts, templates.
Processing step after the main evaluation applying methods like validation and filtering.
Describes how flag values are interpreted (bitwise vs enumerated).
Standard single pass interrogation algorithm.

note.value: Use piv:mask for the numeric bit value and piv:meaning (or skos:prefLabel) for the human-readable label.

definition.value:
An elementary flag concept representing one minimal, indivisible condition
that may be assigned to data points in a PIV dataset (e.g., active, masked, filtered).
Each Flag corresponds to a single power-of-two mask value that can be
combined with others by bitwise OR operations to form composite flag values.
Method used, to replace outliers.
Method to replace vectors identified as invalid by interpolating from surrounding data.

Refers to one or generally many synthetically generated (modelled) tracer particles, also called seeding particles. Its parameters should be described via m4i:hasParameter. The source code generating the particles should be stated via codemeta:hasSourceCode.
Software tool to perform Particle Image or Tracking Velocimetry evaluation.

A PIV multiple pass interrogation window, which uses the local integer displacement in a subsequent interrogation pass by offsetting the interrogation windows. This increases the signal-to-noise ratio of the correlation peak as unmatched particle images are avoided.
Processing step creating a PIV mask
Flag values can be combined using bitwise OR; atoms are recovered via bitwise AND with each piv:mask.
Object that helps an agent perform an action (e.g., John wrote a book with a pen), i.e., an object of the relation schema:instrument or m4i:hasTool
Points to a method that is used within a given processing step
